# Arattai Chat — Backend (Java / Jakarta Servlets)

REST + WebSocket backend for the Arattai chat frontend. Servlets handle request/response APIs; Jakarta WebSocket handles realtime. Kafka does async persistence, notifications, and AI; Redis handles presence, caching, and cross-instance fan-out.

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer              | Choice                                        | Notes                                     |
|--------------------|-----------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| Runtime            | Java 21                                       | LTS                                       |
| Web                | Jakarta Servlet 6.0 + Jakarta WebSocket 2.1   | Tomcat 10.1+ (`jakarta.*`, not `javax.*`) |
| Build              | Maven, WAR packaging                          | Deploy to Tomcat                          |
| Relational DB      | MySQL + HikariCP                              | Users, groups, subgroups, device tokens   |
| Message Store      | Cassandra (DataStax Java driver 4.x)          | High write throughput                     |
| Cache / Presence   | Redis (Lettuce)                               | Pub/Sub for cross-instance fan-out        |
| Message Broker     | Kafka (`kafka-clients`)                       | Async persist, notifications, AI          |
| Object Store       | S3 / MinIO (AWS SDK v2)                       | Media; DB stores only the URL             |
| Auth               | JWT RS256 (`auth0/java-jwt` or `jjwt`)        | + Refresh tokens in Redis                 |
| JSON               | Jackson                                       | DTO (de)serialization                     |
| AI                 | Provider abstraction (OpenAI / Claude)        | Swap behind one interface                 |

