## REST Endpoints (Servlets)

```
# Auth
POST    /api/auth/signup                    name, email, password, username
POST    /api/auth/login                     → { accessToken (JWT 1h), refreshToken }
POST    /api/auth/refresh                   refreshToken → new accessToken
POST    /api/auth/logout                    Invalidate refresh token

# Users
GET     /api/users/me
PUT     /api/users/me
GET     /api/users/{id}

# Conversations & Messages
GET     /api/conversations                  Chat list (from conversations_by_user)
GET     /api/chats/{chatId}/messages        ?before={messageId}&limit=30 — history paging

# Groups
POST    /api/groups                         Create group
GET     /api/groups/{id}
POST    /api/groups/{id}/members
DELETE  /api/groups/{id}/members/{userId}
POST    /api/groups/{id}/subgroups
POST    /api/subgroups/{id}/members

# Media
POST    /api/media                          Upload → { mediaUrl, meta } (or presigned PUT)
```

> Every `/api/*` call except auth endpoints passes through `AuthFilter`, which validates the Bearer JWT and puts `userId` on the request. Membership is checked per chat before any read/write.

