## WebSocket (`/ws`) — Realtime

Single endpoint, JSON frames with a `type` field.

| Direction | Frame Types                                                   |
|-----------|---------------------------------------------------------------|
| Inbound   | `SEND_MESSAGE`, `TYPING`, `READ_RECEIPT`, `PING`              |
| Outbound  | `ACK`, `MESSAGE`, `DELIVERY_RECEIPT`, `READ_RECEIPT`, `PRESENCE`, `TYPING`, `PONG` |

Handshake is authenticated — pass the JWT in the connect query (`/ws?token=...`) and validate before `onOpen`, because cookies are unreliable cross-origin.

```java
@ServerEndpoint(value = "/ws", configurator = WsHandshakeAuth.class)
public class ChatSocket {

    @OnOpen
    public void onOpen(Session session) {
        Long userId = (Long) session.getUserProperties().get("userId");
        LocalSessionRegistry.add(userId, session);
        PresenceService.markOnline(userId);  // Redis key + TTL, heartbeat-refreshed
    }

    @OnMessage
    public void onMessage(String json, Session session) {
        Frame f = Json.parse(json, Frame.class);
        switch (f.type) {
            case "SEND_MESSAGE" -> MessageService.handleSend(session, f);
            case "TYPING"       -> PresenceService.typing(f.chatId, f.senderId);
            case "READ_RECEIPT" -> MessageService.markRead(f.chatId, f.senderId, f.lastReadId);
            case "PING"         -> PresenceService.heartbeat(f.senderId);  // refresh TTL
        }
    }

    @OnClose
    public void onClose(Session session) {
        Long userId = (Long) session.getUserProperties().get("userId");
        LocalSessionRegistry.remove(userId, session);
        // Presence expires via TTL if no other sockets remain
    }
}
```

