## Cross-Instance Fan-out

One JVM only knows its own sockets. With >1 instance, a message must reach a recipient connected elsewhere. Local registry + Redis Pub/Sub solves it.

```java
// realtime/LocalSessionRegistry.java
static final Map<Long, Set<Session>> sessions = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

// realtime/FanoutService.java
void deliver(List<Long> recipientIds, String payload) {
    redis.publish("chat-events", Json.write(new FanoutMsg(recipientIds, payload)));
}

// Subscriber on EVERY instance, registered at boot
redis.subscribe("chat-events", msg -> {
    FanoutMsg fm = Json.read(msg, FanoutMsg.class);
    for (Long uid : fm.recipientIds)
        for (Session s : LocalSessionRegistry.get(uid))
            if (s.isOpen()) s.getAsyncRemote().sendText(fm.payload);
});
```

