## Message Send Path (with Idempotency)

```
client ──SEND_MESSAGE(client_msg_id)──▶ ChatSocket

  1. Handshake already verified user; check chat membership
  2. Dedup: Cassandra INSERT INTO message_dedup ... IF NOT EXISTS (chat_id, client_msg_id)
       └─ applied=false → redelivery, return existing message_id, stop
  3. Assign message_id = TimeUUID (server-side, ordering-safe)
  4. ACK to sender { client_msg_id, message_id }  → frontend reconciles optimistic bubble
  5. Fan-out to ONLINE recipients via Redis Pub/Sub (low latency, not behind Kafka)
  6. Publish to Kafka topic `chat.messages` (async):
       ├─ persist consumer   → Cassandra messages_by_chat
       ├─ inbox consumer     → update conversations_by_user, bump unread counters
       ├─ notify consumer    → push to OFFLINE recipients (FCM/APNs)
       └─ ai consumer        → only when chat_id starts with ai:
```

> Kafka is intentionally **off** the perceived-delivery path — delivery is the Pub/Sub hop; persistence, notifications, and AI ride Kafka.

